<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_gævzykk" xml:lang="os">
    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma">
        <orth>gævzykk</orth>
    </form>
    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal">
        <orth>gævzukk</orth>
    </form>
    <sense>
        <sense>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>убогий</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>crippled</q>
            </cit>
        </sense>
        <sense>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>бедняк</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>poor</q>
            </cit>
        </sense>
    </sense>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>gævzykk jæ card, gævzykk jæ zond</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>убога его жизнь, убог его ум</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>his life is miserable, his mind is miserable</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/>
                <biblScope>III 206</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>gævzykk jæ card, gævzykk jæ zond</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>убога его жизнь, убог его ум</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>his life is miserable, his mind is miserable</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/>
                <biblScope>III 206</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, из <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>gevšek,
                    gävšäk</w><gloss><q>слабый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>дряблый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>инертный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                ><w>gävšäk adam</w><gloss><q>слабый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="trk"><w/><gloss><q>трус</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>II 1581</biblScope></bibl>). Слово <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_gævz"/> ‘бедный’ (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Сл."
                /><biblScope>384</biblScope></bibl>) — вторичное образование в результате осмысления
        конечного %i-ykk%i | %i-ukk%i как суффикса.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It is probably from <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>gevšek,
                    gävšäk</w><gloss><q>weak</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>flabby</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>inert</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                ><w>gävšäk adam</w><gloss><q>weak</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>coward</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Радлов"
                /><biblScope>II 1581</biblScope></bibl>). The word <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_gævz"/> ‘poor’ (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Сл."
                /><biblScope>384</biblScope></bibl>) is a secondary derivative in the result of the
        perception of final %i-ykk%i | %i-ukk%i as a suffix.</etym>
</entry>
